Hello,

Here is the code to illustrate the problem/issue.
When the button is clicked, all the razor components are rendered.
In the console, the value ```There is a Title``` is present and displayed for all the ```OnAfterRender``` component methods.
But the value ```There is a Title``` is not rendered. The display is always ```There is no Title``` on the screen.
A second click displays the correct value which is ```There is a Title```.
Why does this happen?
The Title parameter of the CCTitle child is changed.
The CCTitle parent is rendered.
But the value ```There is a Title``` is not rendered on the screen.
Is it possible to solve it ? Is it required to use the ```StateHasChanged``` method after the first click? 
Is there somewhere in the official documentation an explanation? Is it by design?
Thanks for any answer.

```C#
Index.razor
<button @onclick="Do">Do</button>
<CCTitle>
    <CTitles>
        <CTitle Title="@title"></CTitle>
    </CTitles>
</CCTitle>

@code {
    private string? title = "There is no title";

    protected override void OnAfterRender(bool firstRender)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Index {title}");
        Console.WriteLine("Index OnAfterRender");
    }

    private void Do()
    {
        title = "There is a title";
    }
}
```

```C#
CCTitle.razor
<CascadingValue Value="this" Name="CCTitle">@CTitles</CascadingValue>
<text>@_cTitle?.Title</text>

@code {
    private CTitle? _cTitle;
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? CTitles { get; set; }

    public void Add(CTitle cTitle)
    {
        _cTitle = cTitle;
    }

    protected override void OnAfterRender(bool firstRender)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"CCTitle {_cTitle?.Title}");
        Console.WriteLine("CCTitle OnAfterRender");
    }
}
```
```C#
CTitle.razor
@code {
    [CascadingParameter(Name = "CCTitle")] private CCTitle? CCTitle { get; set; }
    [Parameter] public string? Title { get; set; } 

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        CCTitle?.Add(this);
    }

    protected override void OnAfterRender(bool firstRender)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"CTitle {Title}");
        Console.WriteLine("CTitle OnAfterRender");
    }
}
```
